# st - simple terminal 

My fork of the simple terminal with an intention to customise it with patches.


## Setting up a fork of simple_terminal (st)

### Initial setup

Create an empty GitHub repo (no README, no .gitignore) then clone it:
```bash
git clone git@github.com:YOUR_USERNAME/simple_terminal.git
cd simple_terminal
```

Add the suckless upstream remote:
```bash
git remote add upstream https://git.suckless.org/st
```

Fetch all upstream content:
```bash
git fetch upstream
```

Create local master branch tracking upstream:
```bash
git checkout -b master upstream/master
git push origin master
```

Create your main branch from master:
```bash
git checkout -b main
git push origin main
```

Set main as default branch on GitHub:
GitHub → Settings → Branches → Default branch → switch to main

Verify remotes and branches:
```bash
git remote -v
git branch -vv
```

You should see:
```bash
origin    git@github.com:YOUR_USERNAME/simple_terminal.git (fetch)
origin    git@github.com:YOUR_USERNAME/simple_terminal.git (push)
upstream  https://git.suckless.org/st (fetch)
upstream  https://git.suckless.org/st (push)
main    [origin/main]
master  [origin/master]
```

---

### Daily workflow — adding your own patches/config

Always branch off main for your changes:
```bash
git checkout main
git checkout -b feature/patch-name
```

Make your changes then:
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "descriptive commit message"
git push origin feature/patch-name
```

Then open a Pull Request on GitHub: `feature/patch-name` → `main`

---

### Syncing upstream suckless changes

When suckless releases updates:
```bash
# Update master from upstream
git checkout master
git fetch upstream
git pull upstream master
git push origin master

# Merge upstream changes into main
git checkout main
git merge master
git push origin main
```

If there are conflicts between upstream changes and your patches, resolve them during the merge step.

---

### Branch structure summary

| Branch      | Purpose                                                               |
|-------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `master`    | mirrors upstream suckless exactly, never commit here directly         |
| `main`      | your stable customised version, merges from master + feature branches |
| `feature/*` | individual patches/changes, merged into main via PR                   |


Key principles
* Never commit directly to master — it should always mirror upstream exactly
* Never commit directly to main — always use feature branches and PRs
* master → main is always a merge, never a rebase — preserves upstream history cleanly
* Feature branches always branch from and merge back to main


## Original docs

st - simple terminal
--------------------
st is a simple terminal emulator for X which sucks less.


Requirements
------------
In order to build st you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (st is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install st (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running st
----------
If you did not install st with make clean install, you must compile
the st terminfo entry with the following command:

    tic -sx st.info

See the man page for additional details.

Credits
-------
Based on Aurélien APTEL <aurelien dot aptel at gmail dot com> bt source code.

